<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AVIATION-HUMANFIRSTS25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Robbers, divers, acrobats: Balloonists not first to be first
 &HT;    By Paul Reid
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ After all the misfires, flops, delays,
ill winds and faulty equipment, Brian Jones and Bertrand Piccard
finally made it. No, they weren't passengers on Delta's night
flight from Atlanta to West Palm Beach. They're the hot-air
adventurers who floated around the world tethered to an
18,000-pound balloon. In 20 days.
</P>
<P>
   We offer some past ``firsts'' and a salute to those with the
pluck and luck and brains to make headway for humanity and
headlines for themselves.
</P>
<P>
   1793 _ The first macadam road _ 62 miles _ is built near
Lancaster, Pa. Cost: $465,000, $7,500 per mile.
</P>
<P>
   1797 _ The first parachutist takes the fall.
</P>
<P>
   1849 _ First balloon used for bombardment was sent up over
Venice by the Austrian army.
</P>
<P>
   1859 _ Charles Blondin becomes the first person to cross Niagara
Falls by tightrope.
</P>
<P>
   1866 _ First robbery of a moving train. Frank Sparks and his
gang throw a safe from an Ohio &AMP; Mississippi express.
</P>
<P>
   1889 _ Nelly Bly becomes the first woman to make a world tour
unattended by men, chaperones or busy-bodies.
</P>
<P>
   1895 _ The first auto race takes place near Chicago,
Thanksgiving Day. Average speed of the winner: 7.5 mph.
</P>
<P>
   1958 _ The U.S. submarine Nautilus makes the first underwater
pass of the North Pole.
</P>
<P>
   1960 _ Around the world in 84 days. Underwater. Captain Ned
Beach on the Triton.
</P>
<P>
   1966 _ Bill Verite sails across the Atlantic in 65 days, by
13-foot sailboat.
</P>
<P>
   1994 _ A Florida man makes the deepest ocean dive without
equipment _ 417 feet _ off Key Largo.
</P>
<P>
   And our favorite:
</P>
<P>
   1721 _ First apology by a newspaper for printing incorrect
information. The Philadelphia American Weekly Mercury.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Reid writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
