nonfictional issues in San Francisco right now: First, Mayor Brown
is considering the idea of giving automated teller machines to the
homeless, so citizens don't have to lug around quarters, but can
just run their cards through panhandlers' money machines. Second,
the San Francisco Catholic Archdiocese is criticizing the Board of
Supervisors for voting to close a street in the gay Castro District
on Easter so a bunch of gay guys who dress up as nuns can have a
block party. By ROB MORSE.
