<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    New releases on home video
 &HT;    By Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Mighty Joe Young'' (PG) _ Sure, the mix of
computer-generated effects and animatronic magic really can make
you believe in the mammoth gorilla of the title. But special FX
can't save this lame, noisy remake, which stars Bill Paxton as a
zoologist, Charlize Theron as big Joe's protector and a lot of cars
crashing as the big lug relocates from Africa to Los Angeles.
Priced to buy: VHS, $24.99; DVD, $29.99. Grade: C -
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Firelight'' (R) _ This Gothic romantic drama set in the
1830s could use a little more fire and a lot lighter touch. Still,
it burns with intelligence, craft and pyschological resonance. A
Swiss governess (Sophie Marceau) agrees to bear a child for an
aloof English aristocrat (Stephen Dillane), then disappear from his
life. But their ``business'' arrangement is complicated by feelings
both romantic and maternal. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _ Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
