   Two theoretical physicists ponder the snarly equation of highway
traffic and come up with possible cures for congestion. Using
computer models that treat cars on highways like molecules in a
gas, a team of American and German physicists offers more than a
road paved with good intentions. Robert Kunzig is the European
Editor at Discover magazine.
