</P>
<P>
   ``When people act in selfish ways, it's very hard to achieve a
common goal,'' he says. ``But here the interesting thing is you
have a rather large group of people, they're all being selfish, and
yet they all achieve a very smooth state of running through the
freeway. It's an unintended, global cooperation.''
</P>
<P>
   Nirvana on the freeway?
</P>
<P>
   ``Exactly. For a little while.''
</P>
