<HEADLINE>
UTILITY AND LEATHER CONTRIBUTE TO THE IN LOOK
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By SUZANNE C. RYAN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Stash away your turtlenecks. Dryclean your coats. It's time to
rotate that wardrobe. Here's a style guide to the fashion
industry's definition of up-to-the-moment cool.
</P>
<P>
   UTILITARIAN CHIC: First there were cargo pants. Then messenger
bags. Designers clearly want fashion to be useful. This season is
no exception.
</P>
<P>
   1. Nylon skirt with built-in wallet by designer Kostas Murkudis,
courtesy of Alan Bilzerian. Model: Sonia Garufi, courtesy of Copley
Seven.
</P>
<P>
   2. Cotton dress with four removable tiers to take the wearer
directly from work to a party. By designer Kostas Murkudis,
courtesy of Alan Bilzerian. Model: Sonia Garufi.
</P>
<P>
   THE TOM WOLFE LOOK: White _ not black _ equals power dressing in
1999. Pink is the accent color, even for men.
</P>
<P>
   3. Linen-viscose men's suit, courtesy of Emporio Armani. Model:
Damon, courtesy of Copley Seven.
</P>
<P>
   4. Men's three-quarter-length rayon pants with rayon tank top,
courtesy of Emporio Armani. Model: Damon.
</P>
<P>
   LIFE-OF-THE-PARTY GEAR: New York's spring runways gleamed with
leather. In New England, there's no reason it can't be worn till
June.
</P>
<P>
   5. Leather A-line skirt by designer Ann Demeulemeester, courtesy
of Alan Bilzerian. Model: Sonia Garufi.
</P>
<P>
   CUBICLE FASHION: Don't be a working stiff. Drop the business
suit and opt for a dress.
</P>
<P>
   6. Wool sheath with cashmere cardigan by Ralph Lauren. Handbag
by Kate Spade. Courtesy of Saks Fifth Avenue. Model: Sonia Garufi.
</P>
<P>
   WEEKEND WHY NOTS: Color is everywhere and it's not just pink.
Bright, shiny, iridescent _ that's the rage.
</P>
<P>
   7. Floral cotton pants by Gianfranco Ferre Jeans. Shell by DKNY.
Handbag by Gucci. Courtesy of Saks Fifth Avenue. Model: Sonia
Garufi.
</P>
<P>
   8. Cotton capri pants with tube top by Calvin Klein. Tote by
Ferragamo. Sunglasses by Dolce &AMP; Gabbana. Courtesy of Saks Fifth
Avenue. Model: Anjealetta, courtesy of Copley Seven.
</P>
<P>
   9. Satin pantsuit by Moschino Jeans. Iridescent handbag by Dolce
&AMP; Gabbana. Courtesy of Saks Fifth Avenue. Model: Anjealetta.
</P>
<P>
   NECESSARY ACCESSORIES: Think back to Oscar night. Think ahead to
prom. Glamour is in.
</P>
<P>
   10. Bra-strap headband by Frou, courtesy of Saks Fifth Avenue.
Model: Anjealetta.
</P>
<P>
   11. Jeweled hair pins and headband by Eve Reid, courtesy of Saks
Fifth Avenue. Model: Sonia Garufi.
</P>
<P>
   12. Men's pocketwatch, courtesy of Emporio Armani.
</P>
