   UNDATED _ Unless you were living in Central America 400 years
ago, you've never heard anything quite like ``Guadalupe: Virgen De
Los Indios.'' Slow, soothing, gorgeous in its hymnal softness and
punctuated by percussion and wind instruments such as rocks, log
drums and clay flutes, ``Guadalupe'' is a true hybrid _ part
classical, part world beat. By DAVE FERMAN. Story will move in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
