   CIR-FILM-RESTORATION (Undated) _ Until a few years ago, it was
nearly impossible to fix motion picture film that had been
scratched or stepped on or chewed up by machinery.The development
of high-definition videotape, which can reproduce an image that is
virtually as sharp as that possible with motion picture film, gave
film archivists the tools they needed to do more than just get rid
of scratches. The new technology allows them to virtually recreate
missing frames. By Eric A. Taub. With art.
