<HEADLINE>
SPIFFED-UP SPINACH AND A DRINK-TURNED-DESSERT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Something old, something new this week.
</P>
<P>
   Lou Arnold e-mails looking for a recipe for the spinach at
Abuelo's restaurants. We ran that recipe soon after the restaurant
opened its first Metroplex location on the Airport Freeway.
</P>
<P>
   Another reader e-mails looking for a margarita pie. This version
is from the just-published ``El Paso Chile Company Margarita
Cookbook'' by W. Park Kerr (Morrow, $12.95).
</P>
<P>
   ABUELO'S ESPINACA
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8-10
</P>
<P>
   5 pounds fresh leaf spinach, cleaned, stemmed and chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup smoked bacon, 1/4-inch diced
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon butter
</P>
<P>
   3 cups sliced fresh mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chipotle puree with adobo, see Note
</P>
<P>
   2 cups fresh diced onion
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons fresh minced garlic
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fresh diced red bell pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons Lawry's Seasoned Salt
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces Velveeta cheese, cut into 2-inch cubes
</P>
<P>
   6 ounces cream cheese, cut into 2-inch cubes
</P>
<P>
   2 cups frozen whole-kernel corn
</P>
<P>
   Grated Monterey Jack and Cheddar, combined, for garnish (1/4 to
1/2 cup)
</P>
<P>
   Note: Chipotle chiles are smoked, dried jalapenos. They're sold
canned (in adobo sauce) or dried whole. To puree, simply blend a
canned chile and its clinging sauce in a blender.
</P>
<P>
   Braise spinach in stock pot until limp but still bright green.
</P>
<P>
   Brown bacon in saucepan and drain, discarding drippings. Add
butter to bacon in pan. Add mushrooms, chipotle puree, onions,
garlic, red bell pepper and seasoned salt, and saute until onions
and mushrooms are tender. Stir in Velveeta and cream cheese cubes
and cook until cheese has melted, stirring continuously. Place
spinach in strainer and press to remove all water. Place spinach in
cheese mixture; stir well. Add corn and stir well. Cook an
additional 3 minutes, stirring continually. Place in casserole and
top with grated cheese. Heat in oven until cheese is melted.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving, for 10: 311 calories, 20 grams
fat, 20 grams carbohydrates, 17 grams protein, 53 milligrams
cholesterol, 1,145 milligrams sodium, 59 percent of calories from
fat.
</P>
<P>
   MARGARITA PIE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6-8
</P>
<P>
   4 large egg yolks
</P>
<P>
   14-ounce can sweetened condensed milk
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fresh lime juice
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons tequila
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons minced lime zest
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon triple sec
</P>
<P>
   9-inch prepared graham cracker pie shell
</P>
<P>
   Unsweetened whipped cream, for topping
</P>
<P>
   Thinly sliced lime rounds, as garnish
</P>
<P>
   Position a rack in middle of oven and preheat to 350 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   In large bowl, whisk together yolks and condensed milk. Add lime
juice and whisk for 1 minute. Whisk in tequila, lime zest and
triple sec. Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake until filling is
lightly but evenly set and edges of shell are lightly browned,
about 12 minutes. Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate until
ready to serve, at least 2 hours.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, cut pie into wedges and transfer wedges to dessert
plates. Top each wedge with a dollop of whipped cream, garnish with
lime round and serve immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 360 calories, 16 grams fat, 48
grams carbohydrates, 7 grams protein, 176 milligrams cholesterol,
240 milligrams sodium, 39 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
