perhaps the world's most famous prostate-cancer patient, says Joe
Torre needs to be a patient patient. ``Everybody's different,''
Palmer was saying Wednesday, ``but I think the major advice anybody
who's had this would give Joe is, just take it easy and do what the
doctors prescribe. That's all I tried to do. Just keep up with what
they tell you to do.'' By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-CUBA-BALTIMORE (Undated) _ The Baltimore Orioles will play
the Cuban national baseball team in Havana on Sunday in a
precedent-setting game that has created a stir among the major
league players and coaches who have roots in Cuba. The players are
in their 20's and are defectors; the coaches are men in their 50's
who remember Cuba before Castro. Most are not happy with the
upcoming game. By Murray Chass.
</P>
