   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-DUKE (Undated) _ It has been a long time since a team
entered the Final Four as such a prohibitive favorite. But Duke
appears more than capable of living up to advance billing. With
senior Trajan Langdon firing away from the outside, sophomore Elton
Brand roaming loose in the middle, and a cast of standouts
everywhere in between, the Blue Devils present a diabolical
matchup. By BILL SULLIVAN.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-MICHIGAN-STATE (Undated) _ Tom Izzo has rebuilt the Michigan
State basketball program from the inside out, relying on Michigan
kids to lay the foundation. And the core of this Final Four team
revolves around a group from Flint, Mich., jokingly referred to as
the ``Flint Stones.'' By JEROME SOLOMON.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PLAYERS (Jacksonville, Fla.) _ Last year, Justin Leonard
pulled one of his patented final-round comebacks to steal The
Players Championship from Lee Jantzen. Leonard has been a regular
on the leader board throughout the early part of 1999, but the
Texan is still looking for his first win of the year. And he ranks
as one of the leading contenders heading into this weekend's event.
By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ROCKETS (Dallas) _ The Houston Rockets try to keep their
recent hot streak going as they hit the road to face the Dallas
Mavericks on Wednesday night. By JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
