   BLACK-CANYON _ WASHINGTON _ Moving closer than ever before to
victory in their 10-year battle to redesignate the Black Canyon of
the Gunnison National Monument as a national park, proponents who
believe the change will boost tourism will testify for the
Campbell-Allard bill Wednesday afternoon at a Senate subcommittee
hearing. Witnesses include Gunnison County commissioner Marline
Zanetel and federal officials. The bill would also establish the
Gunnison Gorge National Conservation Area. (Mollison, Cox News
Service).
