   TAX-FOLEY _ WASHINGTON _ Rep. Mark Foley, R-Fla., introduced a
bill Tuesday that would give everyone who pays federal income tax a
5 percent rebate, capped at $500. The rebates would take place only
if the government ran a budget surplus without counting Social
Security taxes. (Lipman, Cox News Service).
