</P>
<P>
   HAITI _ An overcrowded sailboat carrying Haitian refugees sank
in a storm in the Bahamas, and dozens of people, possibly as manay
as 100, are feared dead, Haitian radio stations reported Wednesday.
Passengers panicked when the boat started taking on water off Cat
Island and jumped into the sea to try to swim ashore, radio
stations reported. The accident happened on Saturday, but it took
days for the news to reach Haiti. (Staletovich, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
