Lamar University, a portrait commemorating Jasper dragging death
victim James Byrd Jr. will go on the auction block. ``We've got one
bid from an L.A. real estate man,'' said Ricky Jason, CEO of
Houston-based Colorblind Entertainment and co-owner of the
portrait. ``He bid $1.5 million. We have another bid from a tribe
in Africa that bid $2 million.'' (Lufkin Daily News) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BOLIVIAN-LAWSUIT _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Call this federal court
ruling a joke. On stage was U.S. District Judge Samuel Kent of
Galveston, who ordered a case filed by the Bolivian government
against U.S. tobacco companies sent to Washington, D.C. The suit
had been filed in a Brazoria County state court before it was
transferred to Kent's federal court in Galveston. But what the
judge said in his opinion March 1, not what he did, caused more
than a few guffaws in law offices across Texas as lawyers
circulated it on the Internet in the past few weeks. (McCarthy,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
