<P>
   GAS-DEREG _ Competition for residential customers has gotten
most of the attention so far in Georgia's newly deregulated natural
gas market. But competiton forthe state's 100,000 business
customeers probably been the fiercest because they offer the most
profit potential.Most sought are dry cleaners and restaurants. One
marketer has hired a Korean -American dry cleaner to sell to the
300 cleaners operated by Korean-Americans in the metro area, a
highly sought group. Marketers also seek out businesses with
multiple locations, the larger the better like Home Depot.
According to a consultant who represents such businesses, savings
are running as high as 30 percent. (Quinn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-VIDEOPHONE _ DAYTON, Ohio _ The future of the Internet
is probably not in traditional computers; it will be in other
devices that allow access to the World Wide Web. One such product
will be the Alcatel Internet Screenphone. The screenphone, due on
the market this summer, will allow one-button access to the
Internet from any desktop in your home or office. (Cummings, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ A rundown of the week's financial press. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
