<P>
   BBN-MCCOY-COLUMN _ FORT MYERS, Fla. _ The Atlanta Braves know
when to hold them and know when to fold them . . . which is why
their rotation remains Greg Maddux, Tom Glavine, John Smoltz and
some strong-armed guys to fill out the back of the rotation for a
year or two. That's where guys like Charlie Leibrandt, Pete Smith,
Kent Mercker, Steve Avery, Terrell Wade and Denny Neagle fit in.
Neagle is the latest to do his thing in Atlanta and move on . . .
to the Cincinnati Reds, who are patiently waiting to see him pitch
at full-bore against a full complement of major-league hitters as
he slowly builds arm strength from a weak shoulder. The question
that concerns the Reds should be: Is Neagle another Leibrandt,
Smith, Mercker, Avery or Wade? (McCoy, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
