<P>
   BKC-MICHST _ ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. _ Most of Michigan State's
success this season has come from a quartet of players from Flint,
Mich., a declining industrial city approximately 75 miles from the
school's campus in East Lansing. The leader of the group is guard
Mateen Cleaves, the Big Ten player of the year who is best known
for his involvement in an automobile accident while on a recruiting
trip with rival Michigan as a high school senior. The others are
forwards Antonio Smith and Morris Peterson and guard Charlie Bell.
The longtime friends, all of whom have ``Flint'' tattooed on their
shoulder, have led the Spartans to the Final Four for the first
time since 1979. (Hummer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
