What each side wants.
</P>
<P>
   Possible reefers:
</P>
<P>
   AIR-SAFETY (Washington) _ The National Transportation Safety
Board blames the crash of two Boeing 737s on a phenomenon it says
it can deduce but not explain, two simultaneous failures in a
hydraulic valve in the rudder. It makes what could be one of its
most far-reaching recommendations, that the rudder systems on more
than 3,000 such planes in service should be made ``reliably
redundant.'' By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   LONDON-PINOCHET (London) _ The Law Lords, who constitute
England's highest court, rule that Gen. Augusto Pinochet must
remain in England and face possible extradition to Spain, but they
significantly narrow the charges on which the case will turn. By
Warren Hoge.
</P>
