<HEADLINE>
REPORT: PEPPERDINE'S ROMAR TALKS TO SAINT LOUIS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Lorenzo Romar, who just finished his third season
as head coach at Pepperdine, reportedly interviewed for the vacant
position at Saint Louis University on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Romar would be the fourth candidate to interview at SLU,
according to the St. Louis Post-Dispatch. Illinois State's Kevin
Stallings, Appalachian State's Buzz Peterson and Southern
Illinois-Carbondale's Bruce Weber, all head coaches, have
interviewed for the job.
</P>
<P>
   The Billikens were 15-16 this past season under Charlie
Spoonhour, and 8-8 in Conference USA.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, a secretary in the Pepperdine athletic department
said Romar is scheduled to be out of his office the rest of this
week.
</P>
<P>
   Pepperdine is 42-44 under Romar. The Waves have improved their
won-loss record each season, though, from 6-21 to 17-10 to 19-13
and an NIT appearance this past season.
</P>
<P>
   Romar, 40, was an assistant at UCLA from 1992-96 prior to coming
to Pepperdine. He said in a February interview that he would not
actively seek a job elsewhere and a school would have to make first
contact for him to be interested.
</P>
</TEXT>
